## Installation

Describe how to install your module if it's not obvious. You might use a package manager like npm or yarn to install dependencies.

```bash
npm install @KatKmiotek/my-test-helpers
```

## Usage

How to use the three methods provided by module:

waitForResponse  
Example:

```ts
import { Page } from "@KatKmiotek/my-test-helpers";
import { waitForResponse } from "your-module-name";

const page = /* Initialize your Playwright Page object */;
const urlToMonitor = "https://example.com/api/data";
const expectedStatusCode = 200;

await waitForResponse(page, urlToMonitor, expectedStatusCode);
```

getCognitoToken  
Example:

```ts
import { getCognitoToken } from "@KatKmiotek/my-test-helpers";

const cognitoToken = getCognitoToken();
console.log("Cognito Token:", cognitoToken);
```

printHello  
Example:

```ts
import { printHello } from "@KatKmiotek/my-test-helpers";

const name = "John";
const greeting = printHello(name);
console.log(greeting); // Output: "Hello John!"
```
